## SERUM 2 ENGINE DETAILS

### Architecture Knowledge (learned inside-out)
- Product: Serum 2 — Advanced Hybrid Synthesizer by Xfer Records (Steve Duda)
- Version: 2.0.x ($249, lifetime free updates, free upgrade from Serum 1)
- Formats: VST3, AU, AAX (64-bit only)
- Factory content: 626 presets, 288 wavetables

### 5 Oscillator Types (per slot A/B)
1. **Wavetable**: 2048 samples/frame, 256 max frames, smooth interpolation, dual warp
2. **Multisample**: SFZ format, real instrument library (orchestra/choir/piano/guitar)
3. **Sample**: Loop modulation, rate control (tape stop), slicing, score extraction
4. **Granular**: Position/size/rate/spray, freeze, reverse, pitch-independent time stretch
5. **Spectral**: FFT harmonic resynthesis, transient detection, spectral filtering

### Dual Warp System (30+ modes)
- Classic: Sync, Bend+/-, PWM, Asym, Flip, Mirror, Remap 1-4, Quantize
- FM/Mod: FM from A/B, RM from A/B, AM from A/B, Phase Distortion
- Serum 2: Fold, Wrap, Drive, Filter

### Filters (38+ types)
- Families: MG (Moog), Standard LP/HP/BP/Notch, German LP, Acid (303),
  Comb, Phaser, Flanger, Formant, S&H, Ring Mod, EQ Shelf, Reverb, Ladder, SVF
- Routing: Serial / Parallel / Split A+B
- Features: Drive, Fat mode, Key tracking, Type morph

### Modulation System
- 3 ADSR envelopes with curvature control per segment
- 4 LFOs with custom shape drawing, BPM sync, one-shot/envelope mode
- Drag-and-drop mod assignments with aux source for depth modulation
- Full matrix view

### Effects Rack (up to 10 slots, drag-reorder)
- Core: Distortion, Delay, Compressor, Chorus, Flanger, Phaser, EQ, Filter, Reverb
- Extended: Hyper/Dimension, OTT, Multiband Comp, Pitch Shift, Freq Shift, Bitcrusher, Wavefolder, Tape
- 13 distortion sub-modes (Tube, Soft/Hard Clip, Diode, Lin/Sin Fold, etc.)

### Unison (up to 16 voices)
- 11 modes: Classic, Super, Linear, Chord, Major, Minor, Stack, Spread, Inv Saw, Random

### DUBFORGE Phi Integration
- Unison detune: φ^k × 3.0 cents (symmetric around center)
- Envelope: A:D:R = 1 : φ : φ², sustain = 1/φ ≈ 0.618
- Filter cutoff ladder: 55 × φ^n Hz (55, 89, 144, 233, 377, 610, 987, 1597)
- FM ratio: carrier:modulator = 1:φ (inharmonic growl timbres)
- Effect mix: 1/φ ≈ 0.618 wet
- Macro curve: value^(1/φ) golden response
- LFO rates: Fibonacci divisions (1/1, 1/2, 1/3, 1/5, 1/8, 1/13, 3/1, 5/1, 8/1)

